ntroduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John William Atkins was born in 1475, in London, Middlesex, England as the son of William Edward Adkins. He had at least 1 son with Annia Molyns. He died on 1 April 1540, in his hometown, at the age of 65."},"et":{"1475–1 April 1540":"1475–1. aprill 1540","1475–1540":"1475–1540","1476–1530":"1476–1530","1478–1530":"1478–1530","1500–1540":"1500–1540","1504–1540":"1504–1540","1515–1540":"1515–1540","1453–1475":"1453–1475","1 April 1540":"1. aprill 1540","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1476":"1476","1475":"1475","1530":"1530","1453":"1453","29 Mar 1540":"29. märts 1540","29 March 1540":"29. märts 1540","1540":"1540","29 October 1504":"29. oktoober 1504","1515":"1515","1504":"1504","Wiltshire, England":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, Middlesex, England":"London, Middlesex, England","Chard, South Somerset, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Chard, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","City of London, Middlesex, England, United Kingdom":"City of London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","St George The Martyr, Surrey, England":"Surrey, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1475–1 April 1540":"1475–1. huhtikuuta 1540","1475–1540":"1475–1540","1476–1530":"1476–1530","1478–1530":"1478–1530","1500–1540":"1500–1540","1504–1540":"1504–1540","1515–1540":"1515–1540","1453–1475":"1453–1475","1 April 1540":"1. huhtikuuta 1540",